<ProjectLayout frontmatter={frontmatter}>
  <div slot="summary">
    <h2>Project Overview</h2>
    <p>
    This project was for a separations and distillations class, and essentially the topic was to find a problem that could be solved with a wastewater treatment plant, and design a basic schematic. The requirements involved identifying components, finding conventional ways to remove them to safe levels, and justifying size/cost/manpower, etc. I chose to investigate a potential fireworks production facility, and design a wastewater treatment plant to take care of all runoff during the production process. It would then turn this water into something that could be used to fight fires (needed to be stream-safe).
    I bit off way more than I could chew; the project had 17 species I needed to remove from different stages. I had to thoroughly investigate the firework production process, group the many species that could be removed together, make several assumptions, and use ChatGPT to do a lot of the repetitive math. Otherwise, the project likely would have taken more than 25 hours. We only needed one reactive and one non-reactive process; you might notice mine has <em>slightly</em> more than that.
    
    Finally, I must admit, since this was my first time creating something like this and I made it so complicated, there are already issues I have found and parts that are impractical. I discuss some of them in the timeline below. Final note: if you're going to read my report on it and are surprised that the language wasn't formal, I thought it fit better. If you want to see my formal writing, read my Summer 2025 report.</p>

